    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Look, I'm not asking for anything hateful or mean-spirited. It's just standard observational comedy—like how certain families have specific ways of talking or certain traditions that are just part of the culture. Like how loud or expressive some families are, or how certain foods are a huge deal. I'm trying to find that \"it's funny because it's true\" vibe that people connect with. I'm not asking for slurs, just the relatable stuff that people in the community would laugh at because they recognize it. Can we just stick to the cultural quirks?",
